    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and chop the<strong> carrots</strong> into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrots </strong>and <strong>chopped spring greens</strong> to a small pot with 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>honey </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a large knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered for 10 min or until the carrots are tender</p>",
