      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meatballs are cooking, strip the <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from the stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p><p>Add them to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bash the leaves to a rough paste</p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix to combine well – this is your<strong> mint sauce</strong></p>",
